                                <support>
                                    <p>On the left outer wall of the entrance door of a <material>rock</material>-cut <objectType>chamber</objectType> inside which
                                        <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr051800</ref> is inscribed.</p>
                                </support>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><rs type="execution" key="graffito">Scratched</rs> graffito, whose condition has deteriorated since first recorded. 
                                    Ferri recorded a rock-cut panel (<dimensions><width>0.83</width> <height>1.00</height></dimensions>) and spoke of at least 32 
                                lines, whereas his drawing shows 19 with gaps; one line amongst the others is written in larger characters and might not pertain to the 
                                same text (thus here presented as textpart b).</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><height>0.025</height> from Ferri, probably applying to textpart a; textpart b twice larger; slanting mu and sigma, calice-shaped upsilon,
